    "comment": "Rationale: Figure 4G: Representative eIPSC traces recorded from DG granule neurons in acute DG slices from Sst-IRES-Cre mice.\nFigure 4H: Summary of fitted linear input/output slopes from Figure 4G. Evoked IPSC was significantly reduced in IQSEC3 KD mice, this effect was rescued by addition of DIO-SST.\n\nFigure S6A: Representative images of the cultured hippocampal neurons treated with DMSO, SST, SST+cSST [cyclosomatostatin], and SST+SecinH3 analyzed by staining surface-exposed GABAARγ2 (red) and MAP2 (green).\nFigure S6B: Summary graphs of the effects of SST peptides on surface GABAARγ2 puncta density. Bathing hippocampal neurons with SST increases the surface GABAARγ2 puncta. This effect was completely abrogated by cotreatment with SST antagonist, cyclosomatostatin or inhibitor of the cytohesin ARF-GEF family, SecinH3.\n\nOverall, SST indicates to regulate the GABARγ2 levels in the synapse.. Experimental description: Sst-IRES-Cre mice were purchased from Jackson Laboratory, ME, USA; stock number: 013044.",
